# Cloudflare Pages excludes directories beginning with a dot from a deployment,
# so nothing under /.well-known/ is uploaded (verified on the 2026-07-22 deploy:
# the dotless mirrors served fine while the dotted paths 404'd). These rules
# 200-proxy the canonical paths onto the mirrors emitted by src/lib/well-known.ts.
#
# Use splats, not :placeholders – a `:skill` placeholder rule silently failed to
# match on Pages while the static rules beside it worked. `/blog/* /news/:splat 200`
# is the form Cloudflare documents for proxying.
/.well-known/api-catalog  /well-known/api-catalog  200
/.well-known/agent-skills/*  /well-known/agent-skills/:splat  200
